&lt;p>Covariance is a statistical measure that indicates how two variables change together.&lt;br>
A positive value means the two variables tend to change in the same direction, while a negative value means they tend to change in opposite directions.&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="formula">Formula&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>Covariance is calculated using the following formula:&lt;/p>
