&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="difference-between-covariance-and-correlation-coefficient">Difference Between Covariance and Correlation Coefficient&lt;/h2>
&lt;table>
&lt;thead>
&lt;tr>
&lt;th>Feature&lt;/th>
&lt;th>Covariance&lt;/th>
&lt;th>Correlation Coefficient&lt;/th>
&lt;/tr>
&lt;/thead>
&lt;tbody>
&lt;tr>
&lt;td>Scale Dependent&lt;/td>
&lt;td>Yes&lt;/td>
&lt;td>No&lt;/td>
&lt;/tr>
&lt;tr>
&lt;td>Value Range&lt;/td>
&lt;td>-∞ to ∞&lt;/td>
&lt;td>-1 to 1&lt;/td>
&lt;/tr>
&lt;/tbody>
&lt;/table>
&lt;h2 id="summary">Summary&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Covariance is a fundamental metric for understanding the relationship between two variables.&lt;br>
However, due to its scale dependency, it is often used in conjunction with correlation coefficients for deeper analysis.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>